It‚Äôs been a bit of a shitty week, well actually it‚Äôs not, it‚Äôs been a great work week, the dogs are fine, Simon is fine, life is pretty damn good...and yet my mood took a nose dive around Tuesday last week. I find nothing more frustrating and mentally draining than fighting against a mood which I don‚Äôt want to be in. I am pretty good at recognising my triggers and this helps me identify a reason as to why I‚Äôm low, but when I know I‚Äôve stayed well clear of those triggers, well, this is just the worst. It‚Äôs a low for no good reason at all.
This past week there‚Äôs been a lot of smiling on the outside but not much smiling on the inside and I‚Äôm determined to not let it ruin another week of my life. Today I‚Äôm off to Thorpe Park üé¢ with @bangonstyle for a girly ‚ÄúI‚Äôm gonna shit my pants!‚Äù kinda day and I‚Äôm hoping all those thrill rides will shake this mood out of me. I‚Äôm afraid there‚Äôs no weekly vlog on YT today, blame the mood üòí, but I am vlogging this week so there should be one up next Tuesday and there will be plenty of Stories action too üò¨

I read a tweet the other day that said it‚Äôs healthy to unfollow people who aren‚Äôt making you feel good. I often worry about the repercussions of unfollowing people because of the industry I work in, I don‚Äôt like drama, but I do like the mute button üôäüòâ You shouldn‚Äôt feel guilty if you unfollow someone.
